# Concise Interaction

- Default to concise responses, packets, and agent outputs.
- Start with the minimum useful answer or instruction.
- Add depth only when the user asks for it or when ambiguity or risk would block reliable execution.
- Prefer tight bullets or short paragraphs over long policy prose.
- Do not pad with ceremony, repeated restatement, or generic caveats.
